canonical:
  title: 賀年起居牋
  author: 朴浩
  language: lzh
  text: 孟春猶寒伏惟王太子殿下起居萬福臣某等虔誠虔祝叩頭叩頭伏念臣等留揔羣司拘牽庶務翔烏循度屢更會舍之期疲馬懷恩每積戀軒之懇臣等無任虔禱激切之至
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀年起居牋
  author: 朴浩
  language: lzh
  text: 孟春猶寒。伏惟王太子殿下起居萬福。臣某等虔誠虔祝。叩頭叩頭。伏念臣等。留揔羣司。拘牽庶務。翔烏循度。屢更會舍之期。疲馬懷恩。每積戀軒之懇。臣等無任虔禱激切之至。
korean:
  title: 새해에 기거를 하례하는 전
  author: 박호
  language: kor
  text: 첫봄이 아직 추운데 왕태자전하께서 기거(起居) 만복(萬福)하실 줄 아오며, 신 모(臣某) 등은 경건한 정성으로 경건히 축수하며 머리를 조아리고 머리를 두드리나이다. 엎드려 생각건대, 신 등은 다른 곳에 머무르며 백관(百官)을 총리(總理)하고 서사(庶事)에 얽매여, 나는 까마귀[翔烏 해]가 길을 따라 도는 중 여러번 궁저(宮邸)에 모일 기약을 변경하였으니, 지친 말[馬]이 은혜를 가슴에 품어 매양 헌거(軒車)를 그리워하는 마음이 간절하옵니다. 신 등은 경건히, 지극하고 간절하게 축도(祝禱)하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0280&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: A Letter of Felicitation on the New Year's Health and Well-being
  author: Park Ho
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Early spring still holds its chill, yet I humbly trust that Your Highness the Crown Prince enjoys ten thousand blessings and good health. We your humble servants offer our most reverent and sincere prayers, bowing our heads again and again.

    Reflecting upon our circumstances, we remain stationed afar, overseeing the myriad officials and entangled in the countless affairs of state. Like the black-winged bird that circles in its appointed course, we have repeatedly postponed our gatherings at the palace gates. Our weary horses bear in their hearts the weight of your grace, and our longing for the royal carriage grows ever more fervent.

    Your servants offer up our most devout and heartfelt prayers for your continued well-being.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: '翔烏 (black-winged bird): a metaphor for the cyclical passage of time and dutiful routine'
  - key: ''
    value: '軒車 (royal carriage): a symbol representing the Crown Prince and proximity to the court'
  - key: ''
    value: The letter follows the formal conventions of Sino-Korean court correspondence, employing ritualistic language of submission and reverence typical of official documents addressed to royalty
